@startuml State Machine Events - Event Processing with Timeouts

title State Machine Events: User Event to State Transition to Actions

participant Client as client
participant "StateMachine<S,E,D>" as sm
participant "Event Queue" as queue
participant "TransitionFn<S,E,D>" as fn
participant "Action Executor" as executor

== Event Sending ==

client -> sm: send(userEvent)
note right of client
  E = sealed interface Event
  S = sealed interface State
  D = data class Data
end note

sm -> queue: enqueue(SMEvent.User(userEvent))
note right of queue
  SMEvent<E> sealed hierarchy:
  - User(E event)
  - StateTimeout
  - EventTimeout
  - GenericTimeout
  - Internal(E event)
  - Enter
end note

sm -> sm: dequeue and process

== State Transition Function ==

sm -> fn: apply(currentState, event, data)

alt state match: LockedState
  fn -> fn: pattern match on event
  alt event match: ButtonPressed
    fn --> fn: Transition.nextState(UnlockedState, actions)
  else event match: StateTimeout
    fn --> fn: Transition.keepState(data, actions)
  else other
    fn --> fn: Transition.keepState(data, Postpone)
  end
else state match: UnlockedState
  fn -> fn: handle transitions...
end

== Action Execution ==

fn --> executor: return Transition<S> with actions

executor -> executor: for each action
note right of executor
  Action<S,E> sealed hierarchy:
  - Postpone: save event for later
  - NextEvent(E event): inject event
  - SetStateTimeout(ms): start timeout
  - CancelStateTimeout: stop timeout
  - Reply(reply): send reply back
end note

executor -> executor: execute SetStateTimeout(10000)
executor -> queue: schedule timeout at T+10s

executor -> executor: execute Reply(result)
executor -> client: deliver reply via mailbox

client -> client: receive reply
note right of client
  Can await in ask():
  var result = sm.ask(event, timeout)
end note

sm -> queue: wait for next event
note right of queue
  If StateTimeout fires at T+10s:
  → enqueue SMEvent.StateTimeout
  → transitionFn processes it
  → may change state or repeat
end note
